excerpt: Varadero, covering Cuba’s narrow Hicacos Peninsula, is a popular beach resort town. Along its 20km of Atlantic Ocean coastline is a string of all-inclusive hotel and spa complexes, and a golf course. Near the peninsula’s eastern tip is Reserva Ecológica Varahicacos, a preserve with trails and an ancient burial cave. Parque Josone is a park with a pond and gardens.
detail_description: Varadero is a sought-after beach resort town in Cuba, situated along the stunning 20km coastline of the Atlantic Ocean. The area boasts all-inclusive hotel and spa complexes, a golf course, and natural attractions like Reserva Ecológica Varahicacos with its trails and ancient burial cave. Additionally, visitors can explore Parque Josone, a picturesque park featuring a pond and gardens.
name: Varadero

excerpt: Nature preserve since 1974 with caves containing 2,500-year-old human remains & ancient pictographs.
detail_description: Varahicacos Ecological Reserve, established in 1974, is a nature preserve located on the Hicacos Peninsula in Varadero, Cuba. The reserve boasts abundant flora and fauna, including the Hicaco plant from which the peninsula derives its name. Visitors can spot iguanas, colorful fish, sharks, turtles, and other marine animals. Activities such as diving, snorkeling, climbing and hiking are popular here.
name: Varahicacos Ecological Reserve

excerpt: Time-tested park with bars/eateries, a swimming pool & pedal boat rentals in a bridge-linked lagoon.
detail_description: Parque Josone, established in the 1940s, is a serene haven perfect for leisurely walks. The park features well-maintained gardens, charming fountains, and winding lakes surrounded by swaying palm trees. Visitors can enjoy bars and eateries as well as a swimming pool and pedal boat rentals in the connected lagoon. History enthusiasts will appreciate the mansions transformed into museums or public sites nearby.
name: Parque Josone

excerpt: Oceanside golf complex with 18 holes, club rentals & an elegant bar/restaurant in a 1927 mansion.
detail_description: Varadero Golf Club is a unique 18-hole, 72-par golf course located in an oceanside resort area with lush tropical surroundings and stunning views of the sea. The clubhouse and hotel, Xanadu Mansion, was built in 1930 for a wealthy businessman and has been carefully maintained and restored to its original grandeur. Visitors can rent equipment and enjoy various golf packages at this popular destination.
name: Varadero Golf Club
address: Carretera Las Americas KM 8 1/2, Autop. Sur, Varadero 111321, Cuba

detail_description: Varadero Dolphinarium is a must-visit for nature enthusiasts and families. The town offers historical sites like Mansion Xanadu and the house of Al Capone, but the real charm lies in its natural beauty. Visitors can explore Punta Hicacos Reserve with its Columbian frescoes, relax at Parque Joson, or discover deserted beaches at Mangon lagoon. The dolphinarium provides an unforgettable experience where you can swim with dolphins and enjoy amazing shows.
name: Varadero Dolphinarium
address: Delfinario, Carretera Las Morlas, Parque Natural Punta Hicacos,, Varadero, 42200, Cuba

excerpt: Series of historic caves with ancient art, various geological features & many resident bats.
detail_description: Cueva de Ambrosio is a series of historic caves with ancient art, unique geological features, and a large population of bats. The area offers short hiking trails through scrub forests and is home to the Patriarca, a massive 500+ year-old cactus. The main attraction is the Cueva de Ambrosio itself, adorned with ancient pictograms and inhabited by bats.
name: Cueva de Ambrosio

detail_description: Varadero Street Market, located along Avenida 1, is a popular spot for tourists looking to pick up unique souvenirs and gifts. The market offers a wide variety of items including handmade wooden gifts, Cuban artwork, clothing, jewelry made from coconut or coral, leather goods, and traditional food. Visitors can enjoy bartering with local vendors while browsing through the stalls filled with artisanal crafts such as wooden cigar boxes, straw bags, hats, and more.
name: Varadero Street Market

excerpt: Snug museum with a wraparound porch displaying period furniture & displays on local history.
detail_description: The Museo Municipal de Varadero is a charming museum housed in a traditional Cuban wooden villa, showcasing period furniture, old home decor items, and exhibits on the local history. The museum's collection may be of less interest compared to the beautiful old building itself, which is a well-maintained blue-and-white two-story wooden structure with gingerbread trim and a red-tile roof. Visitors can take guided tours to gain insight into the pre-revolution history and ways of living in this resort town.
name: Museo Municipal de Varadero

detail_description: Nestled on the vibrant entertainment strip, The Beatles Live Music Bar and Grill is a must-visit for those seeking a laid-back atmosphere filled with fantastic tunes. This lively venue features talented bands performing captivating covers of iconic rock hits from the 70s, 80s, and early 90s. As you sip your drink and soak in the ambiance, you'll be surrounded by memorabilia celebrating the legendary Fab Four.
name: The Beatles Live Music Bar and Grill

detail_description: La Casa del Ron, also known as the 'House of Rum,' is a must-visit destination in Varadero for rum enthusiasts. This charming establishment offers an immersive experience in Cuban rum culture, featuring a vast selection of authentic rums, including aged classics and innovative blends. Visitors can embark on a tour to learn about the rum-making process and enjoy expert guidance from knowledgeable staff. Additionally, La Casa del Ron serves as a prime location to purchase various Cuban rums, including flavored varieties.
name: La Casa del Ron

excerpt: Stately hotel in a colonial-style mansion by the sea, offering a restaurant & unlimited golfing.
detail_description: Xanadu Mansion, also known as Dupont House, is a stately colonial-style hotel located by the sea in Varadero, Cuba. The mansion dates back to the 1920s and offers a unique blend of historical elegance and modern luxury. It was once owned by the Du Pont family and has hosted distinguished guests like Winston Churchill.
name: Xanadu Mansion (Dupont House)

detail_description: If you're looking for a lively and unique nightlife experience in Varadero, Snack Bar Calle 62 is a must-visit. Located right in front of the entertainment strip, this bar offers a vibrant atmosphere with live music shows and professional dancers that attract both locals and tourists. The road leading up to the establishment is even closed off at night to create a makeshift dance floor.
name: Snack Bar Calle 62

detail_description: La Casa del Habano is renowned as one of the top cigar stores globally, offering a luxurious experience for aficionados. It features an extensive selection of renowned brands such as Partagas, Hoyo de Monterrey, Ramon Allones, Bolivar, and the complete range of Cohibas. In Cuba, prices are standardized across all stores for cigars and rum. The store also accommodates both individual purchases and larger orders.
name: La Casa del Habano

excerpt: Park & square near the beach with an expansive array of services, eateries & vendors.
detail_description: Parque de Las 8000 Taquillas is a lively park and square located near the beach in Cuba. It offers a wide range of services, eateries, and vendors for visitors to enjoy. The park features various stores with typical Cuban offerings, including ATMs for convenience. Additionally, it houses a small shopping mall with diverse stores that cater to different preferences. Visitors can explore the area and find everything from souvenirs to clothing items.
name: Parque de Las 8000 Taquillas

detail_description: Havana 60 Classic Cars Tours offers a unique way to explore Havana in vintage convertibles. The tours operate like regular taxis, allowing visitors to customize their trip and visit the sights they want. Customers have praised the informative and English-speaking guides, as well as the comfortable and charming vintage cars. Additionally, the company provides convenient airport pick-up and drop-off services, making it easy for travelers to start their Cuban adventure.
name: Havana 60 Classic Cars Tours

detail_description: Iglesia Santa Elvira is a historical church located in the heart of Varadero, Cuba. The church stands as a testament to the area's rich cultural heritage and offers visitors a glimpse into its storied past. With its stunning architecture and serene atmosphere, Iglesia Santa Elvira provides a peaceful retreat for travelers looking to explore the region's history and immerse themselves in its traditions.
name: Iglesia Santa Elvira

detail_description: Los Caneyes is a must-visit craft fair in Varadero, offering traditional crafts and souvenirs for all tastes and budgets. Bargaining is common here, but supporting the local economy by accepting the prices is encouraged. This popular fair attracts tourists with its wide range of items including wooden structures, ceramics, paintings, jewelry, hats, and other regional handicrafts. It's known for being one of the largest craft fairs in Varadero and features friendly artisans offering interesting crafts.
name: Los Caneyes

excerpt: This popular beach features fine white sand fringed by palm trees & many tourist services.
detail_description: Playa Varadero, also known as Playa Azul by locals, is a renowned beach in Cuba located just a short drive from Matanzas. This 12-mile stretch of white sandy shores and turquoise waters offers the perfect setting for sunbathing, swimming, and engaging in water sports. The beach is lined with palm trees and offers various tourist services. It's a popular spot for snorkeling to view abundant fish in the clear blue waters.
name: Playa Varadero

excerpt: Many resorts & tourist attractions are found on this peninsula known for its spectacular beaches.
detail_description: Hicacos Peninsula, also known as Varadero, is a stunning destination in Cuba renowned for its breathtaking beaches and tourist attractions. The peninsula extends over 20 kilometers into the Atlantic and is home to numerous resorts and entertainment venues. Despite its narrow width of about five hundred meters, visitors are always within walking distance of the magnificent white-sand shores.
name: Hicacos Peninsula

detail_description: Nestled in a natural cave, Cabaret La Cueva del Pirata offers a one-of-a-kind disco experience with its unique setting and natural acoustics. The club features a diverse music selection including Latin, reggaeton, and international hits. Once known as a refuge for Caribbean pirates, the cozy nightclub now hosts live music shows and Cuban dances.
name: Cabaret La Cueva del Pirata
address: Km 12 Carretera Las Morlas, Varadero, Cuba

detail_description: Parque Central Varadero is a charming city park located near the Varadero open-air market, offering a diverse array of handicrafts and souvenirs for visitors to explore and purchase.
name: Parque Central

detail_description: Salsa Suárez is a popular restaurant in Varadero, Cuba, offering a diverse international menu to cater to various tastes. The establishment boasts a plant-filled patio that enhances its laid-back ambiance and excellent service. It features an innovative menu with options for vegans, gluten-free eaters, Cuban cuisine enthusiasts, and those seeking international fusion dishes. Professional mixologists craft classic Cuban drinks at the bar-restaurant.
name: Salsa Suárez

detail_description: Located on a rooftop terrace with a romantic and cozy ambiance, La Vaca Rosada is a renowned restaurant offering a delightful dining experience. The menu features an exquisite fusion of local and international dishes, including delicious seafood and charcoal-grilled meat. The open-air setting provides a relaxed atmosphere for enjoying meals while taking in the surroundings. With its welcoming service and popular reputation, this restaurant is a must-visit spot in Varadero for those seeking an inviting Cuban dining experience.
name: La Vaca Rosada

detail_description: Located in the historic center of Varadero, La Vicaria is a popular government-run restaurant known for its delicious Creole food and international cuisine offerings. The restaurant, built entirely of wood and guano in traditional style, offers an excellent quality-price ratio, making it one of the most economical options for dining in Varadero. Its outdoor patio is particularly popular among budget travelers seeking light and inexpensive bites.
name: La Vicaria

excerpt: Laid-back beachfront lodging offering eateries, 2 outdoor pools & a playground, plus a nightclub.
detail_description: Playa Caleta is a charming beachfront destination that offers a relaxed atmosphere, perfect for those looking to unwind. With its inviting eateries, two outdoor pools, and even a playground for the little ones, it caters to families and couples alike. The property also features a vibrant nightclub for evening entertainment. While enjoying the sun-soaked days at Playa Caleta, visitors should be mindful of potential power outages during stormy weather—especially if traveling in the rainy season.
name: Playa Caleta

detail_description: Don Alex is a highly recommended restaurant located just off the main strip in Calle 31, Varadero. Visitors praise its high-quality and flavorful dishes, with the lasagna being particularly outstanding. The ambience of the garden patio adds to the dining experience, and early arrival is advised as it tends to fill up quickly. The menu offers a variety of options including pizza, grilled fish fillet, whole grilled fish, beef tips, steak, and pork chops.
name: Don Alex
address: Calle 31 N° 106 e/1ra y 3ra Ave, Varadero, Cuba

detail_description: Marina Varadero is a bustling hub offering various activities and attractions. Visitors can hop on the Double Decker buses for a scenic tour of the peninsula, taking in the sights of resorts and downtown Varadero. The marina also serves as a departure point for catamaran trips to Cayo Blanco, where guests can enjoy snorkeling, lobster lunch, and unlimited drinks. Additionally, Marina Varadero features trendy stores with international fashion brands housed in vibrant Caribbean-style buildings and hosts a small street market.
name: Marina Varadero

detail_description: Centro Comercial Hicacos is a unique commercial center located in downtown Varadero. Unlike typical tourist markets, this center features stores catering to the local community, including a grocery store and a pharmacy. Situated partially underground, it offers a modest yet comprehensive selection of shops that can meet various traveler needs. Its central location at Parque de las 8000 Taquillas makes it convenient for visitors to access essentials such as clothing and authentic Cuban rum.
name: Centro Comercial Hicacos

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Varadero, Casa del Chocolate is a delightful café that specializes in serving up exquisite mugs of Baracoan chocolate, which perfectly balances sweet and bitter flavors. With both indoor and outdoor seating options, it creates an inviting atmosphere reminiscent of a charming French café. The friendly staff enhances the experience with their warm hospitality, making every visit feel special.
name: Casa del Chocolate

detail_description: Palacio de la Rumba is a popular spot situated on Las Americas Avenue in Varadero, Cuba. It offers a typical Caribbean nightlife experience with great music and ambiance, making it an ideal choice for a night out with friends. Despite its relatively small size, the venue is well-known for hosting Cuban salsa music orchestras every weekend, and the entry fee includes access to an open bar. Visitors can expect to immerse themselves in the rich history of Cuban rumba while enjoying the vibrant atmosphere.
name: Palacio de la Rumba

detail_description: Cabaret Continental is a fun and exciting night club with great music and amazing vibes. The staff are incredibly friendly and welcoming, always following the procedures for Covid to make sure everything is clean and organized. The night club is perfect for groups of friends who want to have a great time together.
name: Cabaret Continental

detail_description: When visiting Varadero, be sure to explore the vibrant nightlife scene, with popular spots like Bar Calle 62, Discoteca La Bamba, and La Comparsita. La Comparsita is an open-air club that offers live music, salsa dancing, karaoke, and amateur comedy performances in a colonial-era courtyard setting. It's a lively venue that strikes a balance between being a bar, dance club, and cabaret.
name: La Comparsita

detail_description: Mambo Club Angel Disotuar is an iconic Cuban night club where you can dance the night away to some of the island's most popular music. With unlimited drinks included in the entry fee, it's a great place to let your hair down and have some fun. The club regularly puts on great live shows, so be sure to check out their schedule for upcoming performances.
name: Mambo Club Angel Disotuar

detail_description: Downtown Varadero, also known as Playa Azul, has a rich history dating back to 1555 when it was just a small fishing village. During the day, the city exudes tranquility, but at night it comes alive with numerous restaurants, shops, cafes and bars lining its seemingly endless streets. Visitors can explore the area by taking a tourist hop on/off bus or enjoy leisurely walks with plenty of dining and drinking options.
name: Downtown Varadero

detail_description: Experience some of the most breathtaking snorkeling at Coral Beach, located about 20km west of Varadero. The underwater world here is a spectacle of vibrant colors and diverse marine life. To reach the snorkeling sites, you'll embark on an hour-long boat trip from the peninsula. Local dive centers offer excursions for a fee, providing all necessary equipment such as life jackets, fins, masks, and snorkels without valves.
name: Snorkeling

detail_description: Parque Central may be smaller than its counterpart, Parque Josone, but it has its own unique charm that draws visitors in. This delightful park features a vibrant handicrafts market where you can discover an array of artisan creations alongside typical souvenirs and trinkets. As you stroll through the park, don’t miss the opportunity to admire the two impressive monuments that add character to this lovely space.
name: Parque Central

detail_description: Playa Varadero is a renowned beach destination located about 80 miles east of Havana, Cuba. It boasts bright blue waters and stretches of white sandy beaches lined with all-inclusive resorts. The sand is not overly fine, and there are plenty of public umbrellas along the first 5-6 kilometers before the hotel zone begins. Sunbeds are available for a small fee. The beach and seabed consist mainly of sand with minimal presence of other elements like grass or shells.
name: Playa Varadero

detail_description: La Rampa is a must-visit gem in Varadero, renowned for its mouthwatering lobster served in a cozy, homey atmosphere that feels welcoming and friendly. This casual eatery has become quite popular among locals and tourists alike, making it wise to plan your visit during lunch or at off-peak dinner times. Diners rave about the exceptional lobster dinner featuring three succulent tails paired with rice, garlic butter, and a fresh salad—an experience not to be missed!
name: La Rampa
address: Calle43,entre 1era ave y, Avenida Playa, Varadero, Cuba

detail_description: Nestled just 30 meters from the shimmering shoreline, the Delightful WIFI House offers a perfect blend of comfort and convenience for beach lovers. While you can indulge in luxurious all-inclusive resorts nearby, this charming abode provides an authentic experience with its cozy atmosphere. Explore vibrant nightlife options and discover fascinating natural reserves that are just a stone's throw away.
name: Delightful WIFI House 30m from the Beach

detail_description: Galería Espacio 34 is a captivating blend of museum and art gallery, showcasing distinctive Cuban artistic expressions through an array of mediums such as photography, paintings, and sculptures.
name: Galería Espacio 34

excerpt: Quaint, historic church overlooking the sea known for its rustic, Colonial-era architecture.
detail_description: Saint Elvira Church is a charming historic church with a rustic, Colonial-era architecture that overlooks the sea. It's a friendly local Catholic Church known for its Sunday service at 11am in Spanish and an amazing choir group. The church accepts donations to support local families, and the best times to donate items are on weekdays from 9am to 12pm or before/after Sunday service.
name: Saint Elvira Church

detail_description: Galeria Ceramica Varadero is a charming ceramic art gallery located in the heart of Varadero. The gallery showcases a wide variety of beautifully crafted ceramic pieces, including colorful vases, intricate sculptures, and decorative tiles. Visitors can explore the vibrant displays and admire the craftsmanship of local artisans. The gallery offers a unique opportunity to appreciate Cuban artistry and take home a one-of-a-kind souvenir.
name: Galeria Ceramica Varadero
